<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-11-24T00:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-11-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="245" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d245">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.0011/11–2448: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-11-24T00:00:00-05:00">November 24,
                                    1948—midnight</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1702. Personal for Stuart. Madame Chiang<note n="27" xml:id="d245fn27">Wife of Generalissimo Chiang Kai-shek, President of the Republic of
                                China.</note> has just spoken to me by telephone. She plans
                            immediate departure by air for temporary visit Washington. Several
                            others in party. Notify me soonest complete info on party and itinerary
                            so appropriate entrance arrangements can be made.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>